JAPAN
Dong Kingman, the award winning Chinese-American artist, travels the world sketching and painting
the beautiful, the monumental and the picturesque His watercolors grace more then forty
permanent museum and private collections in the USA and abroad
JAPAN is a land of controsts. it can display the most neon-lit, skyscrapered and expressway-lined
face, yet finds its inspiration in the quiet beauly of the graceful for Gate and Mt. Fui pictured here.
The Japanese can run their trains at lightening speed, yet spend hours on a small conversational
courtesy Here you will find graceful perfection and formality contrasted with vigorous commerce.
Among the many styish hotels in the capital city of Tokyo is the Keio Plaza Inter-Continental.
Pan Am serves Tokyo on its Round-The-World flights and nonstop daily from New York, San Francisco,
Los Angeles, Honolulu, and Hong Kong. Oscka is served nonstop from Honolulu
